<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,258,1978]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
Male imago. Length (mm): body, 6.0–6.5; fore wing, 6.0–7.0; hind wing, 2.9; cerci, 17.0–20.0; fore leg, 3.6. General coloration yellowish, widely shaded with gray (
<figureCitation box="[798,899,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 167 – 170" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[257,1322,202,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[246,1329,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 167 – 170. Male imago, general view, dorsal: 167, C. dasilvai sp. nov.; 168, C. zunigae sp. nov.; 169, C. pereirae sp. nov.; 170, C. janae sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838480/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Fig. 169</figureCitation>
). Head completely shaded with black dorsally, brownish gray on gena, antenna (except for hyaline flagellum) and ventrally. Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1299,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 167 – 170" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[257,1322,202,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[246,1329,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 167 – 170. Male imago, general view, dorsal: 167, C. dasilvai sp. nov.; 168, C. zunigae sp. nov.; 169, C. pereirae sp. nov.; 170, C. janae sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838480/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Fig. 169</figureCitation>
). Pronotum translucent, completely shaded with gray, darker on anterior portion, medial line, and margins; prosternum yellowish white, shaded with gray; propleura anteriorly grayish, posteriorly black. Mesonotum yellowish, shaded with gray on medial line, parapsidal sutures, and between 
<collectionCode box="[829,879,655,679]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15543" name="Parasitic Seed Plants" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">PSP</collectionCode>
; pleura and sterna yellowish white, shaded with gray; sutures above coxa blackish; furcasternum shaded with gray. Metanotum yellowish white, shaded with gray medially. Legs. Fore leg completely shaded gray, slightly paler at base of tarsomeres; middle and hind legs whitish, shaded completely with gray. Wings. Membrane hyaline, except C and Sc areas shaded with brownish gray, veins hyaline, except C, Sc, and R1 brownish. Hind wing hyaline, except C and Sc areas very slightly shaded with gray. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[278,375,837,862]" captionStart="FIGURES 167 – 170" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[257,1322,202,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[246,1329,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 167 – 170. Male imago, general view, dorsal: 167, C. dasilvai sp. nov.; 168, C. zunigae sp. nov.; 169, C. pereirae sp. nov.; 170, C. janae sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838480/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Fig. 169</figureCitation>
) whitish translucent, widely and strongly shaded with gray on terga, except on pleural folds. Abdominal sterna translucent white, shaded with gray, slightly darker on medial line and inner margin of gill sclerites. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[374,513,909,934]" captionStart="FIGURES 68 – 76" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[265,1305,209,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[260,1326,193,1805]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 68 – 76. Male adults. Campsurus zunigae sp. nov.: 68, genitalia of imago, v. v.; 69, genitalia of subimago, l. v.; 70, detail of penes of imago, l. v. Campsurus pereirae sp. nov., imago: 71, genitalia, v. v.; 72, detail of pedestal, v. v.; 73, detail of penes, v. v.; 74, genitalia, l. v. (forceps omitted). Campsurus janae sp. nov., imago: 75, genitalia, v. v.: 76, detail of penes, l. v." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838452/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Figs. 71–74</figureCitation>
): yellowish white; sternum IX with truncate hind margin (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1244,909,934]" captionStart="FIGURES 68 – 76" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[265,1305,209,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[260,1326,193,1805]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 68 – 76. Male adults. Campsurus zunigae sp. nov.: 68, genitalia of imago, v. v.; 69, genitalia of subimago, l. v.; 70, detail of penes of imago, l. v. Campsurus pereirae sp. nov., imago: 71, genitalia, v. v.; 72, detail of pedestal, v. v.; 73, detail of penes, v. v.; 74, genitalia, l. v. (forceps omitted). Campsurus janae sp. nov., imago: 75, genitalia, v. v.: 76, detail of penes, l. v." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838452/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
), medial line and hind margin black; pedestal of each side touching basally, with apically acute parastylus (not visible in 
<figureCitation box="[1339,1423,945,970]" captionStart="FIGURES 68 – 76" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[265,1305,209,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[260,1326,193,1805]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 68 – 76. Male adults. Campsurus zunigae sp. nov.: 68, genitalia of imago, v. v.; 69, genitalia of subimago, l. v.; 70, detail of penes of imago, l. v. Campsurus pereirae sp. nov., imago: 71, genitalia, v. v.; 72, detail of pedestal, v. v.; 73, detail of penes, v. v.; 74, genitalia, l. v. (forceps omitted). Campsurus janae sp. nov., imago: 75, genitalia, v. v.: 76, detail of penes, l. v." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838452/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
), round inner corner strongly projected; forceps short and translucent, shaded with gray; base of main lobe of penes sclerotized, strongly expanded laterally and proximally, with dorsal surface finely granulated (arrow in 
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,1017,1042]" captionStart="FIGURES 68 – 76" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[265,1305,209,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[260,1326,193,1805]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 68 – 76. Male adults. Campsurus zunigae sp. nov.: 68, genitalia of imago, v. v.; 69, genitalia of subimago, l. v.; 70, detail of penes of imago, l. v. Campsurus pereirae sp. nov., imago: 71, genitalia, v. v.; 72, detail of pedestal, v. v.; 73, detail of penes, v. v.; 74, genitalia, l. v. (forceps omitted). Campsurus janae sp. nov., imago: 75, genitalia, v. v.: 76, detail of penes, l. v." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838452/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
), apical 1/3 narrowing abruptly, rounded and curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[861,948,1053,1078]" captionStart="FIGURES 68 – 76" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[265,1305,209,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[260,1326,193,1805]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 68 – 76. Male adults. Campsurus zunigae sp. nov.: 68, genitalia of imago, v. v.; 69, genitalia of subimago, l. v.; 70, detail of penes of imago, l. v. Campsurus pereirae sp. nov., imago: 71, genitalia, v. v.; 72, detail of pedestal, v. v.; 73, detail of penes, v. v.; 74, genitalia, l. v. (forceps omitted). Campsurus janae sp. nov., imago: 75, genitalia, v. v.: 76, detail of penes, l. v." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838452/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
); secondary membranous lobe translucent, slender and cylindrical. Caudal filament translucent whitish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,258,1978]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
Female imago. Length (mm): body, 9.2; fore wing, 9.0; hind wing and cerci broken. Similar to male imago, except pigmentation more distinct and few other differences, as follows. Thorax. Pronotum shaded with gray, except pale transverse line between anterior and posterior portions, and pale longitudinal sublateral band; medial line concolorous with rest of notum. Mesonotum additionally shaded gray on anterior triangular mark (after mesonotal protuberance). Middle and hind legs shaded more slightly with gray. Wing membranes yellowish. Abdomen ventrally shaded only submedially and laterally on sterna VII–IX; sternum VIII with small anteromedian subquadrate socket (
<figureCitation box="[380,463,1341,1366]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 93" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,342,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1418,337,1885]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 93. Campsurus povilla sp. nov., male imago: 85, genitalia, v. v.; 86, detail of pedestals, v. v.; 87, detail of penes, v. v. Nymph: 88, left mandibular tusk, detail of inner tubercles; 89, left mandible, occlusal view (the basal part and molae were displaced during slide preparation; 90, same, detail of apex; 91, right mandible, occlusal view. Female abdominal sternum VIII with detail of socket: 92, C. povilla sp. nov.; 93, C. zunigae sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838456/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
). Caudal filaments translucent whitish (all except basal segment lost).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,258,1978]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Egg. Length, 250 µm; width, 200 µm. Yellowish with whitish polar cap. Polar cap relatively large (width 0.7× maximum width of egg).</paragraph>
